Summary: small, bright light low in north northwest sky that seemed to burn out
divs: sighting detailssitting in my home i noticed a small but bright light in a dark sky in the north or north\northwest sky just a bit above the tree line. it was much brighter and larger than any of the stars that were abundant in the higher sky. i don't know when it first appeared but i noticed it about 9:07 pm eastern. it may have risen in the sky, i'm not sure but it began to slowly fade in brightness at about 9:13 pm and by 9:15 had slowly faded to darkness\nonexistence. because of the brightness and lowness in the sky, i initially thought it was some kind of suspended fireworks launched over the country club development to my north. as time passed, it was apparent that it wasn't because of the duration of illumination, which was at least 5 minutes.
